<h2 id="760">10. Setting up labels</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Item labels are attached to an item or to the item packaging. Labels can contain information about the price, contents, etc. Label templates allow you to define the size position of the item parameters and order parameters that you wish to print on individual labels.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="3300">10.1. Creating a label template</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to create a label template. You can create up to 10 label templates.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Creating a label template:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » System settings » Item » Labels</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Expand the <strong>New template</strong> area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings as desired. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-create-label-template">Table 22</a>.<br>
<strong><em>Tipp:</em></strong> Save X and Y coordinates for all values that you want to be shown on the label.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The label template is created.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
