<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="360">21.4. Filtering by categories</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Category</strong> tab, you filter for items of a specific category.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Filtering items by category:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the search area, click on the <strong>Categories</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on a category to display all of the items in this category.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Or:</em></strong> To filter by subcategories, expand a category and click on the subcategory.<br>
→ The items found are displayed in the item overview.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as described below to search for items in all of the categories again.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Deactivating the category search:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Filter</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Deactivate the <strong>With category</strong> filter.<br>
→ The next search finds items in all of the categories.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="370">21.5. Filtering by client</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Client</strong> tab, you can search for items of a specific client or a category of the client only. You can also search for items that are not set as available for a client (store). The filter is applied based on the setting <strong>Available</strong> in the <strong>Categories</strong> tab of the variation.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Filtering items by client (store):</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the search area to the left, click on the <strong>Client</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on a client.<br>
→ The items available for this client is displayed in the item view.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Or:</em></strong> Expand a client and click on a category.<br>
→ The available items found in this category is displayed in the item overview.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Filtering items not available for a client (store):</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the search area, click on the <strong>Client</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the option <strong>Not available</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on a client.<br>
→ The items that are not available for the filtered client is displayed in the item overview.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Or:</em></strong> Expand a client and click on a category.<br>
→ The items that are not available for the filtered category is displayed in the item overview.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="380">21.6. Searching for variations within items</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Filters help you search for items. Attribute filters are loaded into the filter list dynamically.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Searching for variations within an item:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
