<h2 id="820">27. Using serial numbers</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In plentymarkets you can set up serial numbers for items to uniquely identify every item sold. Serial numbers ensure traceability of an item in case of errors or problems.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="830">27.1. Entering serial numbers</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter each serial number individually or import large quantities of serial numbers using the data import function.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Entering a serial number:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the item.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Serial number</strong> icon in the toolbar.<br>
→ The <strong>Serial numbers</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a serial number in the <strong>New serial numbers</strong> area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the serial number.<br>
<strong><em>Or:</em></strong> Press Enter to save the serial number.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Saved serial numbers are shown in the overview. The serial numbers are highlighted in green and have the status <strong>FREE</strong>. For serial numbers that are already in use, the order number is shown under <strong>status</strong>. The order number is highlighted in red.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Importing serial numbers</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can create large quantities of serial numbers at once with ElasticSync. For further information about importing serial numbers, refer to the <a href="/en/data/importing-data/ElasticSync#sync-serial-number">Importing data with ElasticSync</a> page of the manual.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="840">27.2. Searching for and editing serial numbers</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <strong>Serial numbers</strong> area of the window, you search for certain serial numbers and edit existing serial numbers.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Editing a serial number:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the item.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Serial numbers</strong> in the toolbar.<br>
→ The <strong>Serial numbers</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a status.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong><em>Optional:</em></strong> Enter the serial number into the search field.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Search</strong>.<br>
→ The filtered serial numbers is displayed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the additional settings. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-edit-serial-numbers">Table 49</a>.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
