<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="850">27.3. Exporting serial numbers</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Export your serial numbers in a CSV file.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Exporting serial numbers:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the item.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Serial numbers</strong> in the toolbar.<br>
→ The <strong>Serial numbers</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the status in the <strong>Export serial numbers</strong> area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the field separator.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Export</strong>.<br>
→ The serial numbers is exported in a CSV file.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_assigning_serial_numbers">27.4. Assigning serial numbers</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Serial numbers are assigned automatically with the help of an event procedure. The item needs to have been completely paid for before this can happen. The serial numbers will be displayed on the invoice that corresponds to the order. Set up an event procedure which automatically assigns a serial number once the order was fully paid for and the order status <strong>incoming payment: complete</strong> was assigned.</p>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title">Setting up an event procedure</div>
<div class="content">
